gov.nist.secauto.decima.core.assessment.result

Interface ResultStatusBehavior

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultResultStatusBehavior

    public interface ResultStatusBehavior
    Used by the DefaultAssessmentResultBuilder to determine if results pertaining to a given requirement are considered to be relevant to the results set produced by a group of assessments.

    Implementations of this class are required to be immutable.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean isInScope(Requirement requirement)
      Implementations of this method are used to determine if a given requirement is relevant to the results produced by the collection of assessments contributing to the result set.

    • Method Detail

      • isInScope

        boolean isInScope(Requirement requirement)
        Implementations of this method are used to determine if a given requirement is relevant to the results produced by the collection of assessments contributing to the result set. Results that are found to be out-of-scope (return value false will result in the ResultStatus.NOT_IN_SCOPE status.
        Parameters:
        requirement - the requirement to consider for scoping
        Returns:
        true if the requirement is in scope for the assessment results, or false otherwise
